Totally, we reviewed 761 records of patients with severe COVID-19 and identified 151 patients who had an IHCA during the study period of 40 days. After exclusions, a total of 136 patients were resuscitated and documented using the Utstein template (Fig. 1
). The characteristics of the included patients are shown in Table 1
. Of these patients, 110 (80.9%) were aged over 60 years and 46 (33.8%) were women. The most frequent comorbidity was hypertension (30.2%), followed by diabetes (19.9%) and coronary heart disease (11.0%) (Table 1).
